{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDgzMDM3ODI3", "number": 7755, "title": "Add commands for showing all panes", "bodyText": "Intent\nFixes #5775\nKeyboard-only users need a way to activate all the panes in the UI. Many of the ephemeral panes shown in the Console panel did not have these.\nAlso, having a direct way to show all of these (sometimes rare) panes is helpful for accessibility testing (and testing in general).\nApproach\nAdded commands for these, in a new submenu of the View menu (\"Show Other Panes\"). Also makes them available in the Command Palette, of course.\nMoved the existing \"Show Find in Files\" command to this submenu, and added the existing command (which wasn't in the main menu) for activating Presentations pane to the menu, but only shown if the Presentation pane exists. Similar behavior already happens for the Build tab.\nQA Notes\nThis PR only covers showing the panes, ensuring we are correctly giving them keyboard focus is tracked separately in #5652.\nHere is the fully populated menu (from a Package project that has a Presentation in it). Confirm that \"Show Build\" and \"Show Presentation\" only appear when in a buildable-project and/or you have previewed a presentation. The rest of the menu items will always appear.\n\nHere's how the Console panel looks with every pane displayed (open source, Pro would add the Launcher tab, too). This isn't new, just harder to do prior to adding these commands. If you need instructions on how to make these appear without using the new menu commands, let me know, I've got notes.\n\nVerify that the commands display and select the correct pane. They should also restore the Console panel if it has been minimized.", "createdAt": "2020-09-09T18:21:09Z", "url": "https://github.com/rstudio/rstudio/pull/7755", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "7e732318df12839160aea342ccce1f5ff629cfb6"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2020-09-10T19:05:58Z", "author": {"login": "gtritchie"}, "t